            "body": "Was refering to this - However, vim.wo changes both the global value and the local value, unless using double indexing, in which case it only changes the local value..\n\nYou implying that setting throught vim.wo is different than vim.wo[0][0] ? (Assume Current window and buffer)\n\nVim.wo.wrap = false - will do it for the entire window and any buffer shown, but it will also mutate vim.go.wrap ? \n\nVim.wo[0][0] = false - that sets the wrap only for the buffer for the current window ? If buffer is shown in another window, it will inherit that other windows wrap ? This will not change vim.go.wrap ?",
